data.text: BRÍAN F O’BYRNE is currently shooting Kurt Sutter’s THE ABANDONS, a western for Netflix, and recently wrapped on the feature film CONCLAVE with Ralph Fiennes, John Lithgow, Stanley Tucci and Isabella Rossellini, directed by Edward Berger. He is a BAFTA winner for LITTLE BOY BLUE, an Emmy nominee for MILDRED PIERCE opposite Kate Winslet, a Tony winner for FROZEN and a five-time Tony nominee (including his acclaimed work in John Patrick Shanley’s DOUBT and the plays of Martin McDonagh). Other recent highlights: feature film TWIG, and Showtime limited series THREE WOMEN, and Netflix feature film THE WONDER opposite Florence Pugh. Brían lives in Sligo, Ireland and has dual citizenship in the US and EU.
